channel.title: Are You Interested In The Stars?
channel.description:
I am.
I think it's only in England, but on the 30th April if you look up to the sky on a flat landscape at dawn, you will see the cresent Moon, Venus, Mecury(?), Jupiter (right on the horizon, hence you need a flat landscape) and Mars just above Jupiter. I'll post a picture in a minute.
